description: Looking for all Big data enthusiasts! This is a group for anyone interested in data and big data in all its beauty. Its an open forum to enable people to discuss all the various incarnations of big data and the technologies that can/will support it. We will look at Hadoop for sure (cloudera, hortonworks, EMR, etc.), Amazon (and all its various bits and pieces - S3, Aurora, DynamoDB, etc.), Azure (and its varied offerings - HDInsight, etc.) as well as other new big data technologies (Spark, Solr, Vertica, etc.) . We will meet once a month in Holborn areas as its so central - will look for a bar - 5 - 8pm. A few ideas and open discussion at the start and on with networking and beer drinking.

name: Social Data
description:
This is a meetup about the use of social data.

Like me you may be wanting to use Social data (aka Social media data, big data, unstructured data) to drive insight.

You may be asking questions like:

    What social data should I use and why?

    What can I learn from others who have used social data successfully in their organization?

    What are the key trends in the use of social data?

    Where can I meet with social data publishers face to face?

    What tools can I leverage to analyze?

    How do I integrate social data into my organization?

It's all very well hooking into the Twitter streams and collecting a bunch of Facebook likes but what do we do with the data when we've got it?

So no matter whether you're a budding social media marketing guru, a data scientist, a Chief Data Officer, or a product czar - this meetup is for you.

name: hackameetup
description: Here at hackameetup, we're all about three things - Beers, Pizza and Hackers. We meet once a fortnight bringing along CTO's, industry experts and awesome companies. Our group is for all tech enthusiasts, coders and non-coders and is a great opportunity to meet likeminded people and chat with some of the best and brightest in the community. We look forward to seeing you soon.

name: LaFosse DevOps
description:
This meetup is for IT executives, DevOps evangelists, and technical specialists to share insights, build relationships, and learn how to drive the behavioural changes needed to achieve a DevOps culture.

Each event, we share 2-3 short presentations by invited industry leading speakers, Q and A session, and a chance to network and discuss ideas over a few drinks.

We have started this event as we are huge endorses of DevOps! 

Having worked with many leading organisations who are starting the DevOps journey, building structures and cultures within IT teams and driving the behavioural change needed to achieve this - We wanted to share this insight, inviting industry leaders to present and share case studies from within their organisations.

We look forward to meeting you at LaFosse DevOps!

name: STEM Talks at King's College London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in STEM subjects delivered by academics from the Faculty of Natural & Mathematical Sciences at King's College London and our corporate partners.

name: Kontena London
description:
Kontena is an open source, developer friendly container and microservices platform to run applications and services packaged as Docker containers. It's easy to setup, easy to use, scalable and works on any cloud; private, public or hybrid. Through full automation, it requires no maintenance. Kontena comes with built-in load balancer, docker image registry, application secrets management, and more. Kontena provides developers with an out-of-the-box solution that gives them time to focus on what really matters – their own software and applications. Learn more at www.kontena.io

In this Meetup group, we are discussing about Kontena open source project, use cases, integrations and related technologies in the ecosystem.

name: London BIM 4 Analysis Meetup Group
description: This is a group for anyone interested in the latest developments and applications of Building Information Modelling and how it applies to performance analysis for the optimised design and operation of buildings. We will have industry and academic speakers come to present findings from their projects and research. This group will be of interest to Architects, Engineers, Environmental Consultants, building designers, BREEAM assessors, LEED AP, IESVE users, Revit users and students.

name: TechXperts
description: TechXperts provides a platform for IT professionals to come together and interact with today's leading technology vendors. Our aim is to create a strong network for discussion, collaboration and the sharing of ideas around Infrastructure, Middleware, Database and IT Management technologies.

name: Pivotal London - Cloud Native Apps Meetup
description:
Platform as a Service (PaaS) is the here and now for devops focused cloud native apps. Pivotal Cloud Foundry is the core technology behind many popular PaaS solutions on the market from IBM, HP etc. This user group brings together people who are involved, using or want to know about Cloud Foundry and other agile technology from Pivotal.  

This is a group for anyone interested in a more agile approach to developing, deploying, managing and updating the innovative new cloud-native applications which modern businesses needs to survive and thrive. 

People should join this group if they write application code or manage/run/work in IT operations that use or may want to use Cloud Foundry. Its a chance to hear latest news and trends, share stories, learn with hands on experience and network with other Pivotal users. We aim to  have regular meet-ups focusing on specific industries. you can expect to attend hands-on workshops, seminars and talks from Cloud Foundry users and developers.

name: Chatbots London Meetup
description: As chatbots are becoming very trendy and mainstream, it is time that we gather and talk about it. We might still be at a very early stage, new bots are florishing every day and they are rapidly getting more and more accurate and relevant. Yet brands, corporates, e-retailers, customer services, media are all still wondering how to approach it. It seems everyone wants to experiment but everyone wonders which solution to go for. Each month, we will host a panel of speakers from various backgrounds in order to benefit from their experience on the subject, followed by a Q&A session.

name: CoreOS London
description: A meetup around CoreOS - Linux for Massive Server Deployments

name: School of Commoning Events
description:
We are a commons education group based in London, established as a Community Interest Company under UK law.

What is the Commons?

“The social and political space where things get done and where people have a sense of belonging and have an element of control over their lives, providing sustenance, security and independence... Commons are organized around resources that are collectively owned or shared between or among populations. These resources are said to be held in common and can include everything from natural resources to domains of the cultural sphere, e.g.: literature, music, arts, design, film, video, television, radio, information, software and sites of heritage. The commons can also include ‘public goods’ such as public space, public education, health and the infrastructure that allows our society to function (such as electricity or water delivery systems). There also exists the ‘life commons’, e.g. the human genome.” (Wikipedia)


Our Purpose

To benefit society by enhancing individual and collective competences in the protection, governance, and cultivation of commons, as an autonomous partner to the private and public sectors.

name: Bioinformatics London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Bioinformatics, Machine Learning apply to biological data, Multi-omics, Next Generation Sequencing, etc. Bioinformatician, Computation Biologist, People has Machine Learning background, Experimentalist who want to know more about bioinformatics, etc, are welcome. I started this group to meet other biological data analyst.

name: SomaliForce
description:
This is a meetup for Somali professionals in London working in or transitioning into the Salesforce industry. 

The Salesforce community has millions of professionals worldwide and is rapidly growing. The community those that work on all the different parts of the different platforms in the Salesforce ecosystem. This meetup group is part of that community, allowing Somali Salesforce professionals to get together, keeping up to date with a continually evolving platform and the need to learn and share our experiences of best practice, and discover how to best transition into and grow their Salesforce careers. By doing things together the potential for learning is far greater.

There is already a strong Salesforce community centered around London and we would highly recommend joining the London Salesforce Admins and London Salesforce Developer User Groups. However, this group aims to serve the needs of Somali Salesforce professionals in particular by providing a place to meet face-to-face, build new relationships, and share personal experiences. 


The group will welcome members who are new to the world of Salesforce, or who may be considering in becoming a Salesforce professional in the future. 


We look forward to meeting you.

name: JBoss Architect Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Red Hat JBoss Middleware or who wants to meet other users who are using JBoss Enterprise Middleware. The group is open to everyone and is aimed at Architects and Enterprise users and less at Developers, if you are a Developer then please do come along but be aware that there are JBoss User Groups (JBUG) that are aimed more at you.

name: Open IoT London
description: Discussing and experimenting with the Internet of Things via open standards, open data, open source, open hardware and open radio. For hobbyists, makers, hackers, academics and mad scientists!

name: Ember London
description:
Ember London is a community for anyone interested in Ember.js and building ambitious applications in the browser.

We host monthly meetups with talks from contributors, library authors and enthusiasts. The aim is to cover a broad range of topics of interest to beginners and advanced users alike.

name: London SDN & OpenDaylight User Group
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Software Defined Networking, OpenDaylight, Openflow and related technologies like OpenStack etc. All skill levels, network enthusiasts are welcome, whether your are technical, non-technical business folk, or an entrepreneur…

It’s to debate and share experiences on all things SDN, including; hardware, switching, the OpenFlow protocol, controllers, application concepts, industry hype and reality, use cases, business adoption, and many other things…

name: TensorFlow London
description:
Does TensorFlow have the potential to become the engine behind most successful consumer and industrial products of the next 10-20 years? 

Absolutely! A much better question is how, and in what new ways, can we:

a) train more computers to teach themselves by sifting through massive amounts of data coming out of all sorts of places

b) make these computers available through an API to provide a high-quality answer to anyone who is in need. 


Why? Because everyone in need deserves the right answer. 

So.... why don't we standardize & democratize the field with and around TensorFlow, and help change the world!?

What. We are a local micro community of those interested in advancing their knowledge of TensorFlow, its use cases and applications.

How. Join our group for a regular dose of human interaction, conversations, smiles, food and drinks on all things TensorFlow:

• How-To's & Best Practices

• Tutorials

• Models

• Algorithms

• Multi-GPU Autoscaling in the cloud

• Tools & Integrations

We will learn how others solve some of the hard problems that exist in the world around us, and how others make predictive APIs and  applications 

Join the movement. Let’s change the world. 

Because everyone in need deserves the right answer.

You are welcome:)

name: The Intrapreneurs - Truly innovators from within
description: It's been a long time, almost 40 years, since Gifford Pinchot III coined the term of "Intrapreneur". Today we assist to a myriad of startups trying to get traction, led by entrepreneurs following the path of Lean Startup. They follow a big idea with courage enough to at least try once. Some others just don't have the proper support for whatever reason to give it a try, just because life is too hard. Intrapreneurs dream becoming Entrepreneurs but don't know how yet, or just the opposite, no longer have enough energy because they already tried and failed, so need stability within a company, until they can start over. Companies today need talent for innovation, which comes from endeavour for sustainable competitive advantage. If you have the attitude of an entrepreneur but still need stability, or just you enjoy innovating within your company, this is your meetup group. We'll share theory, practice and ideas. Get inspired!.

name: Innovate London
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in hearing about the latest and coolest technologies (Wearables, Internet of Things, Beacons, Arduino, 3D Printing, RaspberryPi, Intel Edison, I.A., Augmented Reality, etc). 

Maybe you are into NodeJS and game development (Corona, Unity) or you just want to showoff your awesome GitHub repo or latest app, Its a place where everyone can share their work, learn new things and get to talk with like-minded people. 

Another goal of the meetup is organize hackathons from time to time and also get surprise guests at every event. Did i mention there will be beer and prizes?

name: London SQL Meetup for Database professionals
description:
If your job involves looking after your organisation's databases, and you know that while the core applications run nicely on Oracle or MySQL, and the BI tools are running on SQL Server, and it won't be long until a new application comes along which requires a MongoDB, Hadoop or Cassandra infrastructure , then this group is for you.

Different tools for different purposes.  And you're expected to have knowledge of all them.  

Expert knowledge. 

24/7.  

365.

This group is there to educated and inform; to connect you to peers that are having similar challenges and can give you guidance; and to connect you to experts that have the luxury of time to get into the details of that latest feature of the newest version of whatever the database might be.

Please do join us.

name: Open Data Science Fellows Program
description:
Open Data Science Fellows Program (ODSFP) is for all of you who want to learn and apply data science. It is a collaborative platform to get together to learn data science, to solve meaningful open data problems, hang out, ask questions, share ideas and have a great time. This is a not-for-profit community program dedicated to the dissemination of data science and to promote open data for social good, organized by Persontyle School of Data Science. 

Open Data + Data Science = Social Good 

You will learn Data Science and apply it to solve real data challenges of social/charity/humanitarian organizations. Exciting opportunity for us to collaboratively engage with each other, the community and issues we care about, and our world. 

“The ability to take data — to be able to understand it, to process it, to extract value from it, to visualize it, to communicate it — that’s going to be a hugely important skill in the next decades.” - Hal Varian 

Follow the program on Twitter @ODSFP

More details about Meetups and Data Activism (If you want to organize Meetup in your country, city, campus, company, etc. Contact the organizer)

name: Fit Tech Collective
description:
WELCOME TO FIT TECH COLLECTIVE

THIS ISN'T JUST ANOTHER TECHNOLOGY MEETUP.  THIS IS THE FIRST STEP IN A MOVEMENT.

WE'RE HERE TO SHAKE THINGS UP IN THE SPORT & FITNESS TECHNOLOGY ECOSYSTEM - WE DRIVE CHANGE BY BRIDGING GAPS, CONNECTING DOTS & BRINGING MINDS TOGETHER.

AT THE FIT TECH COLLECTIVE, WE ARE HELPING ESTABLISHED FITNESS PLAYERS AND STARTUPS MAKE THE MOST OUT OF TECHNOLOGICAL INNOVATION.

WE LOVE & SUPPORT YOUR ENTHUSIASM AND INVITE YOU TO ATTEND ONE OF OUR EVENTS TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE ECOSYSTEM THROUGH DISCUSSION AND DEBATE.  

HERE’S TO DRIVING WHAT’S NEXT!

name: London DevSecOps Meetup
description: We're putting Security in DevOps! The industry has chosen DevOps and Cloud Computing as the next revolution and found that the last frontier of Security stands in the way of greatness. We will meet to exchange and create new ideas on how to leverage the best of the DevOps and SecOps worlds and adopt a new mind-set of inclusiveness and collaboration. Join our events to learn more about a new way of achieving secure innovation at scale without the friction of manual methods and the limits of traditional security.

name: IoTDataViz London
description: As Data Visualization for the Internet of Things (IoT) is still only gaining momentum, there are huge opportunities for those looking to get involved. Join us in exploring the potential and roles that Data Visualization will play across IoT verticals and the resulting products and insights for business and consumers alike. For more information please visit: www.iotdataviz.com

name: The London MySQL Meetup Group
description: Meet MySQL users, developers and DBAs, learn about new technologies and features, share opinions, experience and knowledge - All in the London MySQL Meetup Group. For MySQL, MariaDB, Percona Server and other MySQL-related technologies.

name: IT ñ @UK
description:
Profesionales de las tecnologías de la información, hackers expatriados trabajando en el Reino Unido.

Nos gustaría reunir a todas aquellas personas que tienen pasión alrededor de las tendencias en tecnologías de la información, ya sea software, sistemas, metodologías, etc.

En Londres hay muchos grupos similares, y con éste queremos promocionar y conectar a los profesionales de habla hispana o que están interesados en el español como lengua vehicular.

Queremos proponer las actividades que hemos visto que son interesantes como:

- charlas

- coding dojos

name: London Kaggle Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in getting involved in Kaggle competitions and meeting other people in the data science community. The goals are to get data and computer enthusiasts together to form groups to enter Kaggle competitions and discuss the latest tools & techniques available to the data science community. These goals will be accomplished by holding hackdays every few months, built around Kaggle competitions, and by having a monthly meetup in which users participate in small groups to discuss new ideas within data science or Kaggle competitions.

name: s9s Polyglot Persistence - London
description: This meetup is for all those database administrators, system admins, devops professionals etc who deal with multiple types of databases, and in particular MySQL, MongoDB and PostgreSQL. The purpose of this group is to provide talks and a discussion forums to share best practices and ideas on how best automate and manage mixed open source database environments.

name: App Engine
description:
Meet others interested in developing apps on Google App Engine.

This meetup has a strong programming focus, so talks showing working code and workarounds are actively encouraged.

Each meetup will have a reasonable amount of time for informal lightning talks to show members' work.

name: WP Hooked: WordPress Developer meetups in London
description:
WP Hooked is a forum/meetup for WordPress core contributors, theme and plugin developers to get together and share issues, ideas and tips about WordPress.

If your main interaction with WordPress is through the admin console, if it's something that you install and configure rather than build then this meetup probably isn't for you. There's a long-running "WordPress London" meetup which has a much broader scope and will probably give you what you need.

If on the other hand you relish the thought of getting stuck into writing some php code, you can handle using the theme editor on a live site as an option, or the thought of managing your own servers isn't terrifying, then you've probably come to the right place.

The format of the meetups has yet to be decided, and will evolve as we learn what works and what doesn't.

We welcome speakers from any sphere who can add something to our development

name: Maker Mile
description:
The MAKER MILE is one square mile of open workshops, tech startups, artist and design studios, fabricators, galleries, shops and businesses, centering along Vyner Street between Bethnal Green and London Fields stations. This Meetup is for the businesses and spaces in the Maker Mile to network, share, and communicate.

www.makermile.cc

if we have missed your organisation off the map please send a hi res photo, 300 word description and your address to makermilemap@gmail.com

name: How design saved my life
description:
Inspiring true stories from people who's lives have been changed by and through design. Each edition featuring real and practical examples of how different design practices can change one's life.

Working on the format and future events at the moment. So please do join the group and keep on eye on it as it will most likely kick off soon! Alternatively check out our website: howdesignsavedmylife.com

name: Messaging Bots London
description:
Chat is the new mobile interface ! With the average app losing 75% of active users within the first three days, its not only difficult to drive downloads, but also to retain users. On the other hand, user engagement on messaging platforms such as messenger, slack, telegram, whatsapp is reaching new heights. App boredom + rise of messaging is driving a paradigm shift of the decade! Chat interfaces or bots are redefining mobile interactions.

Imagine ordering a cab, playing your favorite music, getting flight updates, buying new trainers - all from within your favorite messaging app!

This group is for developers, designers, data scientists, growth hackers, content producers,  product geeks and generally curious people

name: Time-Series Databases (TSDBs) London
description: This is a group for developers, architects, DevOps and everyone else interested in using time-series databases for capturing analytics or any other type of information.

name: London PostgreSQL Meetup Group
description: Meet others in your local area interested in PostgreSQL: The World's Most Advanced Open Source Database. Discuss this open source database and share the tips and tricks you've learned using it.

name: Web Analytics Wednesday - London
description:
A meetup organised by Lynchpin and  Cranberry Panda Recruitment. 

A great event with fabulous speakers for the analytics community and those interested in analytics , whether you work as an analyst, developer or in digital marketing. 

This is a meetup to share your knowledge, network and grab an after-work drink. As always we look forward to bringing you great guest speakers, who will share their experiences of the latest hot topics in analytics.

If you have any ideas we will be pleased to take suggestions. This group is vendor neutral and from time to time we might have input from software vendors if we feel it valuable, but you should know you won't be sold too.

name: ZeroMQLondon
description: "How to explain ØMQ? Some of us start by saying all the wonderful things it does. It's sockets on steroids. It's like mailboxes with routing. It's fast! Others try to share their moment of enlightenment, that zap-pow-kaboom satori paradigm-shift moment when it all became obvious. Things just become simpler. Complexity goes away. It opens the mind. Others try to explain by comparison. It's smaller, simpler, but still looks familiar." We're a user group focused on ZeroMQ, messaging patterns, software architecture and what not. And we're based in London.

name: People teaching kids to code in London
description:
A meetup for anyone who teaches programming or electronics to kids: in schools, through after-school or weekend clubs, or even just at home. Teachers, volunteer instructors and parents are all welcome.

We'll share useful tips, techniques and technologies with each other, and hopefully become a bit better at what we do.

There are a number of different groups running coding clubs around London, and we think it would benefit all of us if we could get together every so often to shoot the breeze.

name: Data Analytics & Business Intelligence London Group
description:
Welcome to Data Analytics & Business Intelligence social group.

The purpose of DABI London Group is helping business people to enable a better data insights and working with information. Together with business people we will focus on the data insights challenges, how we work with the data and how to unlock insights in the data. We will be looking on ideas how to get more from Data Analytics and Business Intelligence.

We welcome people from the business who are rather users (all rank users) of the technology than the IT experts. The typical group member is not an IT guy but our group member is from the business having role such as a data analyst; a business analyst; business owner; a entrepreneur; a manager; a senior executive; a business decision maker; but main characteristic is that our group member uses data insights and analytics for driving her/his business. People from marketing, sales, performance management, marketing, business development roles areas are very welcome.

The main goals are:

- Discussing the DA & BI business scenarios business people are challenged now.

- Work-shopping how to address that business scenarios and look on technology how it can help.

- Helping business people to sort out challenges with the DA & BI tools.

- Presenting DA & BI tools features focusing on business drivers aspects.

- Looking on DA&BI challenges and how to address these with the Microsoft BI stack.  

We'll be presenting, discussing, work-shopping about the data analytics, business intelligence, data insights, visualisations and also how to tame the technical tools for addressing business needs.

Because the group organiser has an extensive experience with Microsoft BI stack, this group technology focus is mostly around Microsoft technology (such as Excel, SQL, Power BI, SSAS, SSIS, cubes, Office 365, Yammer and many others tools). But please mind that we don't focus on technical discussions only. DABI London Group is focused on business views and needs with technical aspects and looking how the technology brings the value for business and life.  

If you want to enter group you will be asked 5 simple questions. We appreciate your contribution and we want to thank you for answering the group entering questions. Your answers help us to better define the focus and session agenda.

Looking forward seeing you on our meetups!

Jozef

name: Journocoders
description: Journocoders is a monthly event for exchanging practical advice on coding in relation to journalism, whether that's making an incredible data visualisation, scraping gigs of data off the web or building a novelty Twitter bot.

name: Big Data Behavioral Analytics London
description: This is a professional group about behavioral analytics. Execs working at online consumer platforms involved with eCommerce, gaming, mobile, advertising, FinTech and media will meet to talk about using cohort analysis, path analysis, A/B testing, funnels, CAC and KPI to improve churn, conversion and customer LTV. It's all about behavioral and predictive analytics!

name: Operations Research Meetup - London and South East
description: Long before analytics, data science, simulation modelling, and management sciences, there was Operational Research. An umbrella term for any and all types of analysis, modelling and optimisation designed to drive efficiencies in some system, be it commercial, societal, academic or military. This group brings together practitioners, researchers and enthusiasts interested in OR in its various guises (optimisation, modelling, analytics, logistics, simulation, forecasting etc), offering the opportunity to listen to talks from experts in the field on some of their most impactful projects and research. If you are interested in any of the above and want to meet fellow OR practitioners and researchers, from newcomers to those with decades of experience, then this meet-up is for you and if you aren’t already a member you should consider joining the OR society @ https://www.theorsociety.com .

name: London Quant Club
description: The Quant Club is for anyone interested in quantitative finance and machine learning. We plan regular face-to-face meetings in London where we share ideas and thoughts about quantitative finance. The Quant Club is for people interested in learning more about algorithmic trading. We are going to invite speakers to present their research. A special interest of the Quant Club is the application of machine learning tools for building quantitative trading systems. Our meetings are rather informal in a nice relaxed atmosphere. We are looking forward to meeting with you to jointly build trading systems using machine learning and other techniques.

name: HTML5 CodeShow London
description:
Welcome to the html5 Codeshow! We are a group of hackers/developers/tech enthusiasts who are ecstatic about what the future of the web and mobile apps will bring. For years we've seen what the future might look like via sexy sci-fi films--well now the future is here and it's our turn to make that vision a reality! Join us in sharing our coding knowledge and let's develop ideas together over pizza and beer!

Are you working on a website, mobile web app, or designing a game? What are some of the challenges you’ve encountered that you will need to overcome in order to finish the project? Did you just have a breakthrough moment and would like to share it with the rest of the group? Maybe you’re looking for collaborators or just feedback from fellow hackers?

With a strong emphasis on best practices and problem-solving, this HTML5 meetup series aims at inviting developers to demo projects and interact with an audience of fellow programmers. The goal is to get your questions answered!  We will bring at least one expert speaker on board per session, but we want to keep this meetup really developer-centric.

Everyone is welcome to present at the next CodeShow as long as it's HTML5 related - we only ask you to keep it within 5-7 minutes and to let us know in advance if you wish to present (via personal message or in the comments)

This fun geek event will be as good as we all make it! Bring your hacks and your friends and join us for a night of html5 and its CSS3/javascript/flash/.etc friends!

Look forward to seeing you all there!

name: Advance in your career - Udacity London Meetup
description: In Udacity we want to help you advance in your career or get a new job with courses built by industry leaders like Google, Amazon and Facebook. We would like to help our students in UK meet and support each other in their efforts to achieve their new career goals. Our mission is to bring accessible, affordable, engaging, and highly effective higher education to the world. We believe that higher education is a basic human right, and we seek to empower our students to advance their education and careers. Education is no longer a one-time event but a lifelong experience. Education should be less passive listening and more active doing. Education should empower students to succeed not just in school but in life.

name: Learn Software Development
description:
The aim of the group is to provide a basic grounding in various programming languages, technologies and practices including Java, JavaScript, Android, iOS, Swift, PHP, Ruby, Groovy, test automation,agile development, etc.

You should join this group if you are new to software development and/or want to learn/share knowledge on how to develop software in various programming languages in a fun, friendly environment. To make it even more fun, bring a friend along.

Our tutors are experienced, practicing software engineers with many years of experience in various industries with a shared passion for coaching and sharing their knowledge with aspiring developers like you.

If you are totally new to programming, we encourage you to signup up to a “Computer Programming Overview” session to get an introduction to programming languages in general before deciding which language you will like to focus on.

Happy Coding!

name: JS Monthly London
description:
Javascript evolution has sped up (a lot) in recent years and event the most veterans developers find it hard to keep up with the latest trends. This meetup group aims to bring you monthly bite-sized updates on the world of Javascript along with a healthy dose of nice people, beer and pizza.

* Please use your full name when registering, as some of our venues require a full list of attandees beforehand.

name: Oracle Big Data 4 the Enterprise
description:
The Oracle community meetup for all things relating to Oracle and Big Data / Hadoop / NoSQL within an Enterprise environment.

For less specific and more general Big Data and Hadoop community discussions please see two excellent London meetups:

      Big Data London meetup

      Hadoop User Group UK meetup

Also for a perspective on the business value of Big Data try LonData.

name: CloudDrinks :: London
description:
Drinks + Networking + Cloud Technology! If that's your bag then join us for a social meetup at the coolest bars and offices around Silicon Roundabout.

Catch up over drinks with the best and brightest minds in Cloud at our monthly meetup.

name: London CyberTech
description: We aim to learn, share and collaborate around the latest research and innovation in cyber security technology. London CyberTech is a meetup group for business people looking to protect their digital business, technology professionals interested in cyber security and security professionals interested in the latest technologies and research in their field.

name: #LTM — London TensorFlow Meetup
description:
This meetup is targeted at scientists, software engineers, software architects, open source enthusiasts, and scientists interested in using TensorFlow.

TensorFlow™ is an open source software library for numerical computation using data flow graphs.


Values

1. Success is measured on how much we give back

2. This is about passion, not money. Non-commercial and non-profit event

3. We are all responsible for making a difference

4. Diversity brings the best in us



Code of Conduct

• http://confcodeofconduct.com

name: Data Science Lab
description:
Data Science Lab London welcomes any and all data - experts, professionals, amateurs and newbies!

The group brings together leaders from academia and industry on data science to learn and explore best practices, applications, user cases, methods and tools in data science. We want to facilitate and build an output focused community directed towards practical aspects of data science for big, small and/or complex data.

Meetup schedule will consist of a mix of events including speakers from academia and industry, panel discussions, debates and hackathons.

Come along for lively, stimulating discussions and company (with beer and snacks)!

*The group is agnostic to brand, technology and tools. We only care about the merit and usefulness.

name: Internet of Everything London
description: Meetup for Internet of Things enthusiasts in London. People who are interested in learning, experimenting and creating solutions using this revolutionary technology.

name: DataViz London
description:
Join us for this innovative dataviz meet up, with a focus on design and data!

Our meeting topics will be varied, as we believe that the most interesting things happen at the boundaries of disciplines. Looking at the best creative, interactive and most innovative work in dataviz today, our speakers could be from an art or engineering background.

Enjoy insightful talks, join us for a drink, and the opportunity to connect with the best of the London DataViz community!

name: Creative AI: Applications of AI in Art, Music, Film, Design
description: This is a group designed to bring together artists, coders, designers, technologists and industry professionals to discuss the applications of artificial intelligence in the creative industries - art, music, film, theatre and beyond.

name: Software Meetup Surrey (SMS)
description:
Welcome to Software Meetup Surrey! We're a group of like minded individuals who think software and the many facets of putting software together are more than just a job.

We aim to put meetups together where we have bright minds illuminating the room by giving insightful talks, where we sit and write / test code together over coffee or good beer and where we collaborate on interesting projects. If you have an idea of anything you want to do that's software related come and have a chat and we'll see if we can make it happen!

We are open to anyone who is passionate about software including but not limited to:

• Testers

• Scrum Masters

• Developers

• UX Designers

• Project Managers

• Agile Evangelists

• Hobbyist Hackers

• Anyone else who cares to light a jostick at the Temple of Software...

name: Drupal Show and Tell - London
description:
Cameron & Wilding are the proud organisers of the Drupal Show & Tell events. You can learn more about us here: http://www.cameronandwilding.com/

Head over to our new site, especially for the Drupal Show and Tell events, to see videos of previous talks: http://www.drupalshowandtell.com

We're holding monthly Drupal "Show and Tell" evenings at London South Bank University. Each month we'll be calling on people to present a short Drupal related technical talk to the rest of the group.

Your talk could be on anything from a neat solution you've discovered for a tricky problem to your latest favourite feature of Drupal 8. We aim to have a few talks that last around 15 minutes each (with some extra time for questions and discussion).

You don't have to be a Drupal guru to submit a talk! We're looking for a diverse mix of talks and this is a relaxed atmosphere where people who've never done a Drupal presentation before should feel at home.

The very kind people at London Southbank University have donated a great space for one evening per month. It's the 8th floor of their conference building and has space for about 40 with great views over London.

Tea, coffee and sandwiches will be provided and after the session we'll have a pint or two in the pub across the road, so please join us for that too.

If you're a speaker or you're interested in speaking, there are some practical notes here: http://www.meetup.com/drupal-show-and-tell/...

name: TIBCO Spotfire  User Group
description: We're looking to bring together administrators, authors, data analysts and end users of TIBCO Spotfire, regardless of your discipline or industry. It's our aim to grow the local community around statistical programming, data analysis and visualisation, business intelligence and software development.

name: London Cloudera User Group
description: Cloudera is a proud supporter and sponsor of user/meetup groups around the world focusing on Apache Hadoop, Apache HBase, Big Data, Data Science/BI/Analytics, Java, and Cloudera Manager.

name: StartupBus UK
description:
What do you get when you put 30 strangers on a bus and give them 72 hours to conceive, build and launch a startup? The ride of a lifetime.

StartupBus is a life-changing experience. It's a four day bootcamp across Europe that spans six countries. You have over 1,500 miles of road to conceive, build and launch a startup. A journey to create unbelievable startups and unite the European startup community!


This main purpose of this group is to connect developers, UX specialists and entrepreneurs that want to build amazing products and incredible startups across Europe! Additionally, we introduce what the StartupBus community is and how to take part!


We do this by organising social meetups and talks on the following subjects:

• entrepreneurism, building and growing startups

• developer talks on the latest open-source technology for building products that are easy to scale

• talks from StartupBus alumni about their experiences and how STB helped them in the future


Checkout the Facebook group to photos and info about the previous StartupBus UK events!
https://www.facebook.com/startupbusuk

name: Data Natives London
description:
An upcoming regular event for people interested in Big Data, IoT and FinTech. Whether you are professionals in the field, enthusiasts, or students looking to build your career in that direction, there will be something for you. We'll host interesting talks from industry experts, a focus on both business and technical aspects of theses technologies, with plenty of time for beer and networking!

Data Natives London is organised by Dataconomy Media GmbH.

name: London Counterparty Meetup
description:
Counterparty is a revolutionary peer-to-peer financial platform. 

Open source, and built on top of the Bitcoin blockchain, Counterparty is the world’s first trustless P2P digital asset exchange, betting platform and derivatives market. 

This meetup group is a place for Counterparty enthusiasts to hang out and talk business, but anyone with an interest in the disruptive potential of peer-to-peer finance is welcome, including absolute beginners.

More information - 

• Official website 

• Official forums

name: London Big Data Analytics Meet-up
description: Let's get together to discuss big Data and Analytics. We aim to meet up at least twice per year and promise interesting non commercial talks.

name: POWER and OpenPOWER London Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in the POWER8 architecture and the OpenPOWER foundation. The meetup group will focus on the OpenPOWER Foundation innovations and the POWER8 Scale Out Servers, it will be 'techie'! Join up to get new insights and share information about the slick capabilities the server has and learn more about the exciting initiatives being driven by the collaboration of the OpenPOWER foundation members.

name: Arista Networks London Meetup Group
description: This is a group for everyone who is interested in networking technologies and in particular those people keen to learn about areas such as Software Defined Networks (SDN) network automation and cloud. We will be meeting to talk about innovation on the network and in particular innovations in Data Centre technology. Those people using or interested in using Arista technology in their networks are welcome but that isn't a requirement to attend!

name: MarkLogic User Group UK
description:
The MarkLogic User Group UK is a group for users and/or fans of MarkLogic and those who are interested in learning more about MarkLogic Enterprise NoSQL database technology. We'll host informal events for users to meet, discuss, and share best practices regionally. This is an easy way to meet peers and learn how to get more out of MarkLogic Server. This is your Meetup group, so please tell us what you would like to hear!

Want to know more about MarkLogic?  Read on >>

MarkLogic® is a new generation database platform that enables organisations to get more value from more data than ever before. Global enterprises and governments rely on MarkLogic to power intelligent, high performance applications aimed at analysing data for better insights and also running crucial day-to-day business operations. With MarkLogic, organisations achieve faster time-to-value than was possible with legacy databases, while minimising risk and improving data quality.

MarkLogic is the only Enterprise NoSQL database—a powerful, agile, trusted database that has the speed and scale of NoSQL coupled with the enterprise features required.

· Develop stronger applications faster with a flexible data model using Full-Stack JavaScript, JSON and Node.JS

· Find relevant information easier with lightning fast, built-in search

· Gain more intelligence in the data layer using semantics and bitemporal

· Maintain data resiliency and consistency with ACID transactions, scalability and elasticity, certified security,   and high availability and disaster recovery

name: Insurance Professionals
description:
This meet up will bring together insurance professionals to discuss the disruptive future for insurance.

The group aim is to connect, challenge, and inspire.

name: Analytics Network
description:
The Analytics Network is a special interest group of the professional body, The Operational Research Society. For those with an interest in analytics, in topics such as data science, optimisation, visualisation, Big Data, Regression, Data Mining, Predictive modelling or forecasting, the Analytics Network is intended to be your home within the Operational Research Society (The O.R. Society).

The O.R. Society was established over 75yrs ago, to promote the application of scientific methods to data, to enable decision-making and advice-giving. The O.R. Society has always provided a professional home for those working in both O.R., Analytics and Data Science; this group aims to bring together resources, news, views and information for just that purpose.

name: Argyll Scott London Technology Meetup
description:
A meetup group for all technology professionals working in IT & Technology departments in Commerce & Industry and Financial Services companies of all sizes, particularly within Architecture, Big Data & Analytics, Business Intelligence, Development, Infrastructure teams.  This is a group for people who are looking to attend informative and relevant meetups where engaging speakers share their live experiences and knowledge of current issues and hot topics to create interactive debates, genuine knowledge sharing and networking opportunities.  

We will be hosting regular Meetups where our panel of expert speakers will deliver talks on different themes and issues currently facing technology professionals.   We hope to create thought provoking conversations in our Q&A sessions and ensure that everyone takes away something new from each session.  Aside from great speakers, interesting discussion topics and useful networking opportunities, there is also always pizza and a drink or two to enjoy at the end as well!  Please feel free to sign up as members of our Meetup Group to find out about future events and online discussions as well as have the opportunity to RSVP to event invitations.

Argyll Scott is a specialist international Technology Recruiter which is passionate about building relationships and keeping our market insight updated and accurate.  Hosting these meetups allow our consultants to remain in tune with expert opinions on current key issues and offer an excellent opportunity to maintain relationships with existing contacts and develop new ones.    We very much look forward to seeing you at our next Meetup.

Please feel free to send in ideas of topics and speakers you would like to see on our future events calendar.

name: DevRocket UK
description: This group is for developers interested in learning to choose the best tools to develop their ideas from the database to the mobile UI passing by web performance. All skill and experience levels are welcome. The main aim is to discuss techniques and share experiences over a friendly beverage. Sometimes this will involve watching a presentation.

name: Mapping open data to unlock new insights. London, UK
description:
The UK is leading the world on open government data: 37,500 datasets freely available and counting.

Amongst these, geospatial data has relevance to most sectors. Whether it is business, education, engineering, or health, we use geospatial data to understand and solve problems across space.

Thanks to innovations in the field of web mapping, the entry level for working with this type of data has become accessible to everyone.

Web maps based on open data make amazing business insight and planning tools. Join us to see how you can build your own!

name: London d3js meetup
description: “This is a group for anyone interested in d3js All skills levels are welcome. D3.js is a JavaScript library for manipulating documents based on data. D3 helps you bring data to life using HTML, SVG and CSS. D3’s emphasis on web standards gives you the full capabilities of modern browsers without tying yourself to a proprietary framework, combining powerful visualization components and a data-driven approach to DOM manipulation.”

name: Tech Tuesday London
description:
A monthly meetup hosted on Tuesday evenings, with talks and demonstrations from industry leaders and some of London's most exciting start ups, covering all areas of the data industry. In addition, thought leaders will promote discussions and run workshops with the most innovative and cutting edge technologies. There will also be ample opportunity to socialise and network with like-minded enthusiasts and professionals over food and beverages. These events will be hosted by Keyrus, a specialist data consultancy firm. If you are interested in speaking or contributing to the events, please get in touch at enquires.uk@keyrus.com

Twitter: @KeyrusUK
Facebook: www.facebook.com/keyrusuk
Linkedin: www.linkedin.com/company/bipb

name: Data Engineering London
description: Data Engineers put Data Science into action. We exist where data science and computer science intersect. This meetup is for data engineers, aspiring data engineers and anyone else interested in the field. DataOps, Infrastructure, Architecture, etc.

name: Internet of Things London
description:
Since 2011, we gather once a month to listen to talks from 3 speakers making the internet of things happen. Our talks cover urban infrastructure, smart grid, open hardware, quantified self, open data, environmental monitoring, smart products, smart homes and more.  Anything that puts a networked computer where none has gone before.

Our sponsors are Resin.io , Sherlock by One Fine Stay  & Zuhlke.


If you're new to the topic, have a look at  http://iot.london

Follow us at @iotlondon and use #iotlondon at the meetup to share with others. 

We also send out a monthly newsletter to the group with events, competitions all related to the internet of things. Submit your suggestion to http://iot.london/submit

This meetup is organised and curated by Alexandra Deschamps-Sonsino (@iotwatch) a designer and consultant who has worked in this space since 2007. 


NB: Please be aware that the meetup gets booked online very quickly but no-shows are frequent. One of the many challenges running free events in London :)

name: Analysts Anonymous
description:
Calling all analytical addicts, those of us who are intoxicated by the particular experience of adventure and discovery using novel datasets to help solve intractible problems.

I don't believe I am the only analyst around who frankly doesn't care about any of the 3, 4 or 5 v's, velocity, volume or veracity are not the priority. Rather it is the challenge, exploration, discovery and resolution of problems that provides the impetus.

We are analysts for whom the simpler the solution the better. Those who seek to simplify, but no further than justifiable. Who don't hid behind complication, who would rather be approximately right than accurately wrong. Who see particular software solutions or methods as part of a tool-set rather than badges of honour. For whom the priority is focusing on solving the problems to hand, within the constraints that apply with creativity and innovation.

name: London & International Eris Meetup
description:
Eris Industries makes the tools for developers to build secure distributed computing systems for whatever purpose they can imagine. These tools are the distributed application server, or Decerver, and our bespoke smart contract-enabled, smart contract-controlled blockchain design, called Thelonious. They're ready-to-use, right now, at  https://decerver.io/tutorials . 

This MeetUp group is administered by the corporate bods at Eris Industries and a few independent developers who've taken a keen interest in using our stuff. 

Hang out, build stuff, have fun!

name: Veeam London User Group
description: Veeam is one of the most popular and well known backup software solutions on the market - with 500,000 users worldwide and counting! Come and join us and share your experiences of using Veeam with other people in the world of IT. This will be an informal event, with beer and pizza provided for attendees... Has Veeam worked well within your environment? What are your thoughts about Veeam Availabilty Suite v8? Join other like minded individuals and share your thoughts/ideas! No resellers please, this is an end user event. We look forward to seeing you there!

name: North Kent Web Development Meetup
description:
This meetup group is open to all with an interest in web development and design to discuss tools and techniques useful to both developers and designers. 

The meetup will include at least one presentation followed by Q&A and general discussion. Snacks and drinks will be provided!!! 

We will schedule the meetup as regular as interest and participation allows.

name: LabAgility
description:
This group is for CEO's, scientists, researchers, bio-informaticians and heads of IT

FROM innovative bio-techs and pharma

name: Data Science Clinic: Office Hours
description:
Hi there! I will be doing a series of free informal office hours drop-in session for people who need help with their data, or solutions to specific problems that require machine learning, artificial intelligence or data science. It is broadly aimed at technical and non technical managers, startup entrepreneurs, people wishing to make use of their own business data, or people wishing to make use of open or social media data. During the course of the drop-in session, which will take place in a cafe, attendees will be encouraged to socially discuss their businesses with one another, and share ideas. We may also go out for drinks afterwards.


Areas covered:

- Discussion of available open data

- Big data

- ETL, or pipelines

- Data fusion

- Image, sound, video, or natural language processing

- Deep learning and when to use it

- Predictive analytics

- Geospatial data

- High dimensional data

- Databases, SQL and NoSQL, performance.

- Other. Try me.

- Networking

name: Software Development Manager & Mentorship Group
description: This is a group interested in every thing a software development manager does. We are passionate about our craft and want to explore, support and elevate others.  Our purpose is  to classify what software development managers do, where they fit in different organisations and how they can be more effective.  We will be looking at all aspects from building successful teams , how to be ahead of your team in order to have the correct tools to communicating with stakeholders.  We intend to have Code camps,  presentations ,Testing Camps. Interviewing product owners, designing architecture, defining the test plan, writing the code, testing all types, load, stress, scalability, UI, integration, the delivering to a customer. Real world examples.

name: UK Computer Vision Meetup
description: UK Computer Vision Meetup - an online community for people who are working on Computer Vision, so they can share their information and possibly use other researcher's achievements and prevent the cycle of reinventing the wheel. To accomplish this goal, currently will be listing different source codes, commercial or free softwares and datasets. In addition to those, we will provide information about upcoming events and job openings related to computer vision. Also, we will accept and publish all online books that cover different areas of Computer Vision.

name: Couchbase Virtual User Group
description:
What is Couchbase?

Couchbase is the company behind Couchbase open source project, a vibrant community of developers and users of Couchbase document-oriented database technology. 

Couchbase Server is a packaged version of Couchbase technology that’s available in Community and Enterprise Editions. Couchbase is known for easy scalability, consistent high performance, 24x365 availability, and a flexible data model. 

Companies like AOL, Cisco, Concur, LinkedIn, Orbitz, Salesforce.com, Shuffle Master, Zynga and hundreds of others around the world use Couchbase Server for their interactive web and mobile applications.

name: AWS User Group - London (Media & Entertainment)
description: Using AWS? Thinking of using AWS? In London and working in Media & Entertainment sector? If so, this group is for you! We plan to get together at least 3 times a year so we can share experiences, discuss hot topics and generally try and make our lives easier by using AWS!!

name: OpenTechSchool London
description: OpenTechSchool is a community initiative offering free programming workshops and meetups to technology enthusiasts (learners) of all genders, backgrounds, and experience levels.  It supports volunteer coaches in setting up events by taking care of the organizational details, encouraging coaches to create original teaching material. This material is then openly shared online and can be further developed by contributions from the global OTS community. OTS’ main goal is to create a friendly learning environment where no one feels shy about asking any question. Everyone is invited to participate, whether as a coach or a learner, and get in contact to organize OTS events anywhere in the world.

name: London Containing Bioinformatics & Data Analytics
description:
A group for all those coders and open source champions. Git lovers, Docker enthusiasts, applied Bio-/Health-/Medical-Informaticians and Machine Learners. ELK stack fans, software devs and engineers and UX/UI designers. For all those general computer and data science folks that are interested in meeting like-minded practitioners to chat/rant and play; set some standards, and hopefully, start and do some interesting things with real world applications. 

This meetup is a spin-off and extension of our [Bio in Docker] 2015 Event and more (I hope).  It will evolve depending on input from members. Open to suggestions. We'll get some themes up and running and start meeting up summer time(ish).

It's open to all and any industry/profession. 

More soon... I am  in the early days of planning, but, do come and get involved

Ps. You don't need to be in London or the UK to take part in this group! 

Twitter: @s_j_newhouse

name: London Image Processing Meetup
description: For professionals, students and academics interested in learning about the latest advances in image processing with a friendly group of like-minded people. Diverse and interesting speakers on subjects such as self-driving cars, face recognition, emotion analysis, medical image processing, industrial machine vision, astronomical image processing and robotics. Covering both traditional hand-crafted approaches and machine learning approaches to image processing. Interesting talks with lots of images but no equations.

name: Code Mastery Meetup
description: Anyone who wants to take their software engineering, coding, development or dev-ops to the next level.

name: Agile Data London
description:
Agile Data London is a community of people committed to breaking the obsession of "Big Data" in favour of "Timely" data.

Together we are uncovering better ways of approaching data by doing it and helping others do it. Through this work we have come to value: 

- Hypothesis lead experimentation over predetermined solutions
- Actionable response to events over data reporting
- Building production-ready prototypes over comprehensive IT strategies
- Stream processing over relational databases

Under the banner of "Agile Data", we are seeking to ensure the wider industry and market comes to understand that there are better ways of approaching the problem and opportunities driven by the current obsession with "Big Data".

name: From PhD to Startup Meetup: London
description:
Doing a PhD in a technical subject and interested in startups, but don't really know where to start? Learn about the route from doing a PhD to starting a startup via monthly talks from founders who've been where you are.

Join the International Facebook community here - https://www.facebook.com/groups/PhDtoStartUp/

name: London IBM Mainframe extending their useful life & our jobs
description:
The volume of transactions on IBM Mainframes is increasing, despite misconceptions that these are out of date systems. The challenges this meetup group will consider, is how to extend and improve the functionality of these systems.  At the same time, enhancing the careers of those who do consider such improvements. The areas that I am thinking of are;

1. Virtualization.  How practical is it?  What are the software issues?
2. Re-Platforming. i.e. keep the object code, but move to a new platform, e.g. Linux. 
3. What tools would we lose in both of the above? What could we replace them with?
4. How do we re-tool ourselves, to move from a z/OS environment , to a Linux or Windows environment?
5. Security. Of the underlying platform, operating system, data, and moving to a new commodity, and open environment.
6. Does anyone have anything they can demonstrate?
7. Any burning issues?

Please contribute any ideas, thoughts, advice.

name: Citrix CSP User Group
description:
This is a group for all-things Citrix Hosted Desktops, where Citrix Service Providers can learn how to grow their Service Provider Business. We are a community of business professionals and technicians who meet and share ideas as a Mastermind and learn what others are doing and succeeding with in the CSP Programme in delivering Hosted Desktops (DaaS). Leading figures from the community share their stories, their victories and the ones that got away.  The aim of the CSP User Group is to get local partners together regularly to talk about your experiences, successes, and difficulties with your clients and prospects and to use the mastermind and networking principals to be a resource for technical and business professionals who want to keep pace with the Desktop as a Service arena and related Cloud and Virtualisation technologies. We will aim to have at least one CSP partner or Citrix to present a Success Story, a War Story and updates of course on the business and market trends. We will invite technology partners to speak and include related organisations such as Microsoft, AWS, and other public cloud providers to share their stories too. With 2700 CSP partners worldwide, what matters is that you're talking about Desktop as a Service (DaaS) and related topics that are interesting and important to you. This is not a sales pitch, this is an information sharing and updating opportunity for the community to gather as they need and grow their businesses. The group will also present updates on other events organised by relevant groups, vendors and partners which can help you. We invite specialists and new technologies to present about innovative technology solutions. This group is also structured to enable participants to help each other with solution challenges if necessary. We will also drink some wine and beer and take a snack too. With already 500,000 Citrix CSP Hosted Desktops out there, this is the place to meet, learn and do more business. We are virtuosos because doing Virtual Desktops is an art!

For speaking and sponsorship requests please message via the app

name: London Hack&&Tell
description:
If you've ever visited Hacker News, you've almost certainly seen the "Show HN" or "Ask HN" posts. Well, it's time to get off the Internet and tell us about it face to face. We'll provide you with our honest feedback, you provide us with a great hack, or idea. 

We'll give you 5 minutes to show off your tool, hack, library (did you just write a library to access the Meetup API in Go!?), whatever. We're language and software/hardware agnostic, so it's all fair game. 

After you present, it's an open forum. The audience will ask questions and provide feedback. We want to enable as much participation as possible at these meetups, so you'd better be able to take criticism and dish it out (all within reason of course). N.B. personal projects only, no idea or startup pitching, no commercial plugs!

We're the newly formed London chapter of the multi-city Hack && Tell meetup movement. Show us some love by becoming a member and following us on Twitter (@hackandtellLDN).

name: SoftLayer Cloud
description: This is a group for anyone interested in learning more about SoftLayer, leveraging it to expand your business, integrating it into your operation, exploiting its APIs, etc. All skills levels are welcome. I started this group because the future of computing is Cloud and SoftLayer will play a massive part in that future. Looking forward to exploring the potentials for SoftLayer with everybody.
